###############################################################################
# SPARQL QUERY EXAMPLES (Documentation)
###############################################################################

chatman:SPARQLQueryExamples
  a owl:Class ;
  rdfs:label "SPARQL Query Examples for Organizational Ontology"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """
This organizational ontology enables rich SPARQL queries:

1. WHO REPORTS TO WHOM?
   PREFIX org: <http://www.w3.org/ns/org#>
   PREFIX foaf: <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/>

   SELECT ?person ?personName ?manager ?managerName
   WHERE {
     ?person org:holds ?post .
     ?post org:reportsTo ?managerPost .
     ?managerPost org:holds ?manager .
     ?person foaf:name ?personName .
     ?manager foaf:name ?managerName .
   }

2. WHAT TEAMS EXIST IN ENGINEERING?
   PREFIX org: <http://www.w3.org/ns/org#>
   PREFIX foaf: <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/>

   SELECT ?team ?teamName
   WHERE {
     ?team org:unitOf* <https://ontology.chatmangpt.com/org#EngineeringUnit> .
     ?team foaf:name ?teamName .
   }

3. WHO ARE THE MEMBERS OF BUSINESSOS TEAM?
   PREFIX org: <http://www.w3.org/ns/org#>
   PREFIX foaf: <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/>

   SELECT ?person ?personName ?role
   WHERE {
     ?team foaf:name "BusinessOS Team"@en .
     ?membership org:member ?person .
     ?membership org:memberOf ?team .
     ?membership org:role ?roleType .
     ?person foaf:name ?personName .
     ?roleType rdfs:label ?role .
   }

4. WHO WORKS ON MULTIPLE TEAMS?
   PREFIX org: <http://www.w3.org/ns/org#>
   PREFIX foaf: <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/>

   SELECT ?person ?personName (COUNT(?team) as ?teamCount)
   WHERE {
     ?person org:holds ?post .
     ?membership org:member ?person .
     ?membership org:memberOf ?team .
     ?person foaf:name ?personName .
   }
   GROUP BY ?person ?personName
   HAVING (?teamCount > 1)

5. LIST ALL ROLES IN THE ORGANIZATION
   PREFIX org: <http://www.w3.org/ns/org#>
   PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>

   SELECT ?roleTitle ?description
   WHERE {
     ?role a org:Role .
     ?role org:roleTitle ?roleTitle .
     ?role rdfs:comment ?description .
   }

6. ORGANIZATIONAL HIERARCHY (TREE VIEW)
   PREFIX org: <http://www.w3.org/ns/org#>
   PREFIX foaf: <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/>

   SELECT ?parentOrg ?parentName ?childUnit ?childName
   WHERE {
     ?parentOrg a org:Organization .
     ?parentOrg foaf:name ?parentName .
     ?childUnit org:unitOf ?parentOrg .
     ?childUnit foaf:name ?childName .
   }

7. FIND PEOPLE AT A SPECIFIC LOCATION
   PREFIX foaf: <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/>
   PREFIX vcard: <http://www.w3.org/2006/vcard/ns#>

   SELECT ?person ?personName ?city
   WHERE {
     ?person a foaf:Person .
     ?person foaf:name ?personName .
     ?person vcard:hasLocality ?city .
     FILTER (?city = "Pasadena"@en)
   }

These queries can be executed against Oxigraph or any SPARQL endpoint
to generate real-time organizational reports, validate hierarchies,
and analyze team composition.
  """@en ;
  .

###############################################################################
# COMPANY.YAML CONVERSION GUIDE
###############################################################################

chatman:CompanyYamlConversionGuide
  a owl:Class ;
  rdfs:label "company.yaml to RDF Conversion Pattern"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """
CONVERTING YAML ORGANIZATIONAL STRUCTURE TO THIS ONTOLOGY:

If a company.yaml file existed, it would follow this pattern:

┌─ company.yaml ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ company:                                                                    │
│   name: "ChatmanGPT"                                                        │
│   website: "https://chatmangpt.com"                                         │
│   email: "info@chatmangpt.com"                                              │
│                                                                             │
│   divisions:                                                                │
│     - id: "engineering"                                                     │
│       name: "Engineering"                                                   │
│       teams:                                                                │
│         - id: "businessos"                                                  │
│           name: "BusinessOS Team"                                           │
│           members:                                                          │
│             - name: "Sean Chatman"                                          │
│               role: "Staff Engineer"                                        │
│               manager: "CEO"                                                │
│             - name: "Roberto"                                               │
│               role: "Senior Full-Stack"                                     │
│               manager: "Sean Chatman"                                       │
│                                                                             │
│     - id: "operations"                                                      │
│       name: "Operations"                                                    │
│       members:                                                              │
│         - name: "Slaughter"                                                 │
│           role: "DevOps Engineer"                                           │
│           manager: "Sean Chatman"                                           │
│                                                                             │
│   locations:                                                                │
│     - id: "pasadena"                                                        │
│       name: "Pasadena HQ"                                                   │
│       address: "115 E Del Mar Blvd, Unit 405, Pasadena, CA 91105"          │
│       type: "headquarters"                                                  │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

CONVERSION ALGORITHM (Python-like pseudocode):

def yaml_to_rdf(yaml_data):
    # 1. CREATE ORGANIZATION
    org_uri = f"https://ontology.chatmangpt.com/org#{yaml_data['name'].replace(' ', '')}"
    create_instance(org_uri, org:Organization)
    set_property(org_uri, foaf:name, yaml_data['name'])
    set_property(org_uri, foaf:mbox, f"mailto:{yaml_data['email']}")

    # 2. CREATE LOCATIONS
    for location in yaml_data['locations']:
        loc_uri = f"https://ontology.chatmangpt.com/org#{location['id']}"
        create_instance(loc_uri, org:Site)
        set_property(loc_uri, foaf:name, location['name'])
        set_property(loc_uri, vcard:hasStreetAddress, location['address'])
        set_property(org_uri, org:based_near, loc_uri)

    # 3. CREATE ORGANIZATIONAL UNITS (Divisions)
    for division in yaml_data['divisions']:
        div_uri = f"https://ontology.chatmangpt.com/org#{division['id']}"
        create_instance(div_uri, org:OrganizationalUnit)
        set_property(div_uri, foaf:name, division['name'])
        set_property(div_uri, org:unitOf, org_uri)

        # 4. CREATE TEAMS (Sub-units)
        for team in division['teams']:
            team_uri = f"https://ontology.chatmangpt.com/org#{team['id']}"
            create_instance(team_uri, org:OrganizationalUnit)
            set_property(team_uri, foaf:name, team['name'])
            set_property(team_uri, org:unitOf, div_uri)

    # 5. CREATE PEOPLE
    for person_data in extract_all_people(yaml_data):
        person_uri = f"https://ontology.chatmangpt.com/org#{person_data['name'].lower().replace(' ', '')}"
        create_instance(person_uri, foaf:Person)
        set_property(person_uri, foaf:name, person_data['name'])

        # 6. CREATE POSTS (Role Assignments)
        post_uri = f"https://ontology.chatmangpt.com/org#{person_data['name'].lower().replace(' ', '')}-post"
        create_instance(post_uri, org:Post)
        set_property(post_uri, org:role, lookup_role(person_data['role']))
        set_property(person_uri, org:holds, post_uri)

        # 7. CREATE MEMBERSHIPS
        for team_id in person_data['teams']:
            member_uri = f"https://ontology.chatmangpt.com/org#{person_data['name'].lower().replace(' ', '')}-{team_id}"
            create_instance(member_uri, org:Membership)
            set_property(member_uri, org:member, person_uri)
            set_property(member_uri, org:memberOf, lookup_team_uri(team_id))
            set_property(member_uri, org:role, lookup_role(person_data['role']))

    return rdf_graph

SPECIAL MAPPINGS:

YAML Company Field          →  RDF Property
─────────────────────────────────────────────────
company.name                →  foaf:name
company.website             →  foaf:homepage
company.email               →  foaf:mbox
location.address            →  vcard:hasStreetAddress
division.teams              →  org:OrganizationalUnit (sub-units)
person.role                 →  org:Role
person.manager              →  org:Post (reportsTo) chain
person.teams                →  org:Membership (multiple)
person.email                →  foaf:mbox
person.phone                →  foaf:phone

VALIDATION:

After conversion, verify:
1. All foaf:Person instances have foaf:name (required)
2. All org:Post instances have org:role (required)
3. All org:OrganizationalUnit instances have org:unitOf or org:unitOf* chain back to org:Organization
4. No circular reporting relationships: org:reportsTo paths must be acyclic
5. All referenced roles and teams exist before linking
6. Manager (org:reportsTo) resolves to actual org:Post instances
  """@en ;
  .

###############################################################################
# ONTOLOGY USAGE NOTES
###############################################################################

chatman:UsageNotes
  a owl:Class ;
  rdfs:label "Usage Notes for Organizational Ontology"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """
KEY DESIGN DECISIONS:

1. W3C ORG (MANDATORY):
   - org:Organization: Top-level company
   - org:OrganizationalUnit: Teams, divisions, departments
   - org:Post: Job position / role assignment for a person
   - org:Role: Abstract job title (can be shared across multiple posts)
   - org:Membership: Team membership with optional role override
   - org:reportsTo: Reporting relationships between posts

2. FOAF (MANDATORY):
   - foaf:Person: Every team member
   - foaf:name: Required for all people and organizations
   - foaf:mbox: Email addresses (mailto: scheme)
   - foaf:homepage: Personal/organizational websites
   - foaf:phone: Phone numbers (tel: scheme)

3. vCard (LOCATION INFO):
   - vcard:hasStreetAddress, hasLocality, hasRegion, hasPostalCode, hasCountryName
   - Used for both person and site location information

4. DCTERMS (METADATA):
   - dcterms:identifier: Stable, human-readable IDs (not URIs)
   - dcterms:description: Human-readable descriptions
   - dcterms:issued: When relationship became effective
   - dcterms:creator: Who created the record

5. PROV (PROVENANCE):
   - prov:wasInformedBy: For collaboration relationships

QUERY PATTERNS:

• Hierarchical lookup: Use org:unitOf* (transitive) to find all nested teams
• Reporting chain: Follow org:reportsTo from post to post to build chain
• Team members: Query org:Membership with org:memberOf filter
• Role lookup: Get all posts with specific org:role
• Multi-team members: Count distinct org:memberOf per person

EXPANSION POINTS:

To extend this ontology further, add:
- org:subOrganization for subsidiary companies
- foaf:givenName / foaf:familyName for internationalization
- foaf:workplaceHomepage for team pages
- foaf:interest / foaf:topic for expertise areas
- org:reportsTo chains for approval workflows
- Temporal validity: prov:startedAtTime / prov:endedAtTime for historical org changes
- org:linkedTo for peer relationships (not hierarchical)
  """@en ;
  .

###############################################################################
# END OF ORGANIZATIONAL ONTOLOGY
###############################################################################
